@title Rscript: run an R script at the command line
@created 1497063849846
@weight 0.5

File tree references are relative to where you run the script from (and not where the script is located).

e.g. From folder F in a terminal, if RScript runs the script at F/subfolder/S.R, and S.R refers to the path "A/B/C", it will use F/A/B/C